24/09/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- German Ambassador to Macedonia Irene Hinrichsen praised authorities Thursday (23 September) for bolstering the fight against organised crime. Hinrichsen and Macedonian Interior Minister Siljan Avramovski signed a protocol on Germany's donation of technical equipment -- worth a total of 144,000 euros -- to the ministry's anti-drug unit. The donation includes several vehicles, computers and digital cameras. Hinrichsen reiterated that the fight against organised crime is a key factor in Macedonia's EU integration process. (Makfax, MIA - 23/09/04) 
